The paper discusses the use of scientific imaging techniques for 3D reconstruction and the development of differentiable probabilistic models for this purpose. This involves the use of machine learning algorithms and optimization techniques, which are commonly associated with computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and scientific computing (cs.SI).
